    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Reconditioning - Replacing Valve Seats
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="6">
        <title>Replacing Valve Seats</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <figure id="f2650542" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08103.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Grinding group tool</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air motor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Grinding base</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Grinding wheel</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_108.xml" xrefid="t2650505">grinding group tool</hotlnk>to cut a groove in
                    the valve seat insert.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650543" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Grinding groove in valve seat</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the appropriate size extractor in the valve seat.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650544" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08033.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the valve seat insert</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Lifting bridge</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve seat remover (collet)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Expand collet by threading the shaft into the valve seat remover until it is tight
                    inside the valve seat. Turn T-handle on shaft to pull the valve seat insert from cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650545" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Valve seat insert removed</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Collet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve seat insert</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlock the collet by loosening the threaded shaft. Discard valve seat insert.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a micrometer to measure the diameter of the valve seat insert counterbore at two
                    locations, 90&#176; apart. Average the two measurements to determine the appropriate size valve seat
                    insert to install.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <table id="t265050.5" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="topbot">
                <title>Valve Seat Insert Selection Chart</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.87*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.07*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.08*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Available inserts (int. and exh.)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Ave. dia. of intake counterbore</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Ave. dia. of exhaust counterbore</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Standard</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>40.119 - 40.170 mm (1.5795 - 1.5815 in)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>37.478 - 37.529 mm (1.4755 - 1.4775 in)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Oversize - 0.05 mm (0.002 in)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>40.170 - 40.221 mm (1.5815 - 1.5835 in)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>37.529 - 37.579 mm (1.4775 - 1.4795 in)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Chill the valve seat insert in a freezer for 30 minutes. This will prevent the outer
                    layer of metal from being shaved off during installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650546" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Placing chilled valve seat into head</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align insert over counterbore to avoid misalignment.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650547" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Driving valve seat into place</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a hammer and valve seat installation tool drive the valve seat into place until it
                    is fully seated, see
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_108.xml" xrefid="t2650505" appearance="hottext">Cylinder head and valve
                        special service tools</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grind new valve seats to the specified angles and widths, see
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_SVCPROC0502.xml" xrefid="t2650503" appearance="hottext">Cylinder Head
                        Specifications
                    </hotlnk>
                    in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
